Size. Largest known specimen a female 897 mm TL (measured fresh); the largest paratype (SUML MMLM 018) was measured in 1999 at 896 mm TL (
Compagno et al. , 2005
) and shrank to 878 mm TL when measured a decade later. Of the two known males, one was sexually mature ( 621 mm TL) and the slightly larger holotype was at a late adolescent stage ( 657 mm TL); birth size unknown.
